  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Wireless Mouse for Work in 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 8+ models</div>

      <p>You move your mouse thousands of times a day, and a bad one makes every one of those movements worse. A trackpad is fine for browsing, but for spreadsheet work, document editing, and anything requiring precision, a dedicated wireless mouse is non-negotiable. The good news: the best budget option costs under $20.</p>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Budget</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 8 budget wireless mice based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each mouse was assessed for tracking accuracy, connection reliability, battery life, and comfort based on documentation and feature analysis.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature comparison. Connection reliability was assessed based on manufacturer specifications, and battery life was reviewed per specifications.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Tracking accuracy, click consistency, and connection stability</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Shell rigidity, scroll wheel durability, and button longevity</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-feature ratio against premium alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Pairing, charging convenience, and ergonomic comfort</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Product</th>
            <th>Best For</th>
            <th>Price</th>
            <th>Rating</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
